CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 12, 1956, pg. 3, reads: "Seeworthy!  Going somewhere?  Certainly not, these girls might answer, because they're right here in Pittsburgh where they danced at the Beauticians Convention at the Fort Pitt Hotel.  They're posed atop luggage but all we can gaze at are pretty legs.  They are seeworthy.  Left to right: Genevieve Still, Alberta Thompson and Yvonne Jones. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Genevieve Still, Alberta Thompson, and Yvonne Jones Kemp wearing dresses with full skirts and petticoats, posed with luggage in Fort Pitt Hotel
